IVOLUNTEERI  
The Houston 2012 Foundation is representing the City of Houston in its US bid 
for the 2012 Olympic Games.  Volunteers are needed Thursday, May 11-Tuesday, 
May 16, 2000.  Their duties will include hotel reception, drivers, media 
assistants, and help assembling gift bags.   To volunteer, please call Garry 
Barard at 713.877.6123.

IHAPPENINGSI  
Free Houston Ballet Performance!  On Thursday, Friday and Saturday, May 11, 
12 & 13 at 8 p.m., the Houston Ballet will perform at Miller Outdoor Theater 
in Hermann Park.  Pack a picnic and enjoy the evening as the company performs 
In The Middle, Somewhat Elevated, Three Preludes and Sergeant Early's Dream.  
For more information, please call the Miller Theater Box office at 
713/284.8350 or visit them on-line at 
www.ci.houston.tx.us/departme/parks/millerschedule.htm

Check out Camp Enron on Thursday, May 11th from 11:00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m at St. 
Anne's. Are you looking for a summer camp for your child ages 5-13?  Come 
visit St. Anne's during the camp open house.  Transportation is provided from 
the Enron building.   Call Michelle Kapfer at 713.853.7514 for reservations 
or visit the website at  http://www.kidventurecamp.com/enron.htm for more 
information.

Take the time to save lives: Donate Platelets!  MD Anderson is always seeking 
donations of platelets to help several Enron employees and their families.  
Taxi vouchers will be provided to/from Enron/MD Anderson for donations.  
Platelet donation will take approximately 3 hours.  Whether driving on your 
own or using a taxi, call Michelle Kapfer at 713.853.7514 for information.

IWORKPERKSI
Worried about an older relative?  Whether you're just beginning to think 
about the well-being of an older relative, helping-out occasionally, or 
already acting as a day-to-day caregiver, the LifeWorksc program can give you 
free information, advice, and resources.  Call LifeWorks at 1.800.635.0606 or 
visit 
LifeWorks Online 
http://www.lifeworks.com/login/login.cfm?uid=enron&password=2000

